  "text": "How frequently does hybrid element formation occur? Hybrid element formation has been inferred to explain male recombination [CITATION_1] . However, it has been postulated that hybrid element formation occurs at a reasonably low rate, since the rate of recombination produced by a single P element is only of the order of 0.5-1.0% [CITATION_2] .",
